@startuml user_account_management_communication

!theme plain
scale max 1200 width
title User Management: Block/Unlock Account - Communication Diagram (Sequence + Component Interaction)

note top
  **System Components:**
  - Blazor UI (Admin_UserManagement.razor)
  - Business Logic Service (UserManagementService)
  - EF Core DbContext (AppDbContext)
  - PostgreSQL Database (users table)
  
  **Scenario:** Admin blocks a Teacher account for policy violation
end note

actor Admin #FFFFFF

participant "Blazor UI Component\n(Admin_UserManagement.razor)\n(LearnmateSolution)" as UI
participant "UserManagementService\n(BusinessLogicLayer)" as Service
participant "AppDbContext\n(EF Core ORM)\n(DataAccessLayer)" as DbContext
database "PostgreSQL Database\nusers Table" as DB

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════░
' PHASE 1: LOAD USER LIST
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rect rgb(200, 220, 255)
    Note over Admin, DB
      **PHASE 1: LOAD USER LIST**
      Navigation: /admin/users
    end note
end

Admin -> UI: **1:** Navigate to User Management Page
activate UI

UI -> UI: **2:** OnInitialized() / LoadUsers()

UI -> Service: **3:** GetUsersAsync(\n  roleFilter: "",\n  statusFilter: "",\n  searchQuery: "")
activate Service

Service -> Service: **4:** Build LINQ Query
note right of Service
  db.Users.AsQueryable()
    .Include(u => u.StudentProfile)
    .Include(u => u.TeacherProfile)
    .Where(...)
    .OrderByDescending(u => u.CreatedAt)
end note

Service -> DbContext: **5:** Execute Query (ToListAsync)
activate DbContext

DbContext -> DB: **6:** SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE conditions\nJOIN student_profiles\nJOIN teacher_profiles
activate DB

DB --> DbContext: **7:** User Records (ORM mapped to User entities)
deactivate DB

DbContext --> Service: **8:** IEnumerable<User>
deactivate DbContext

Service -> Service: **9:** Map User [] → UserRowDto []
note right of Service
  foreach User u:
    UserRowDto dto = new() {
      Id = u.Id,
      Email = u.Email,
      Role = u.Role (TEACHER/STUDENT/ADMIN),
      Status = u.IsActive ? "Active" : "Blocked",
      Name = u.StudentProfile?.FullName
             ?? u.TeacherProfile?.FullName,
      AvatarUrl = u.AvatarUrl
    }
end note

Service --> UI: **10:** IEnumerable<UserRowDto>
deactivate Service

UI -> UI: **11:** Bind to table component\nusers = result.ToList()

UI --> Admin: **12:** Display User Management Page
note right of UI
  - Stats cards: Total, Active, Blocked users
  - Filter controls: Role, Status, Search
  - User table with rows
  - Action buttons: Block, Unblock, Delete
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════░
' PHASE 2: ADMIN SELECTS USER & OPENS MODAL
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rect rgb(255, 240, 200)
    Note over Admin, UI
      **PHASE 2: SELECT USER & OPEN MODAL**
      Admin clicks "Block" button on Teacher row
    end note
end

Admin -> UI: **13:** Click "Block" button\non Teacher "John Smith" row
activate UI

UI -> UI: **14:** OpenBlockModal(userRowDto)
note right of UI
  selectedUser = {
    Id: 5,
    Email: "john@teacher.com",
    Name: "John Smith",
    Role: "Instructor"
  }
end note

UI -> UI: **15:** Initialize Modal State
note right of UI
  blockReason = ""
  blockNotes = ""
  formError = ""
  showBlockModal = true
end note

UI --> Admin: **16:** Display "Confirm Block User" Modal\nwith Form Fields
note right of UI
  Modal Contents:
  - User Info (name, email, role)
  - Reason dropdown (Teacher Violation,
    Account Abuse, etc.)
  - Optional Notes textarea
  - Cancel / Confirm Block buttons
end note

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════░
' PHASE 3: ADMIN SUBMITS BLOCK REQUEST
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rect rgb(255, 220, 220)
    Note over Admin, UI
      **PHASE 3: SUBMIT BLOCK REQUEST**
      Admin fills form and clicks Confirm
    end note
end

Admin -> UI: **17:** Select Reason: "Teacher Violation"\nEnter Notes: "Violated T&C Section 3.2"\nClick "Confirm Block"
activate UI

UI -> UI: **18:** ConfirmBlock() handler (click event)

UI -> UI: **19:** Validate Form
note right of UI
  if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(blockReason)) {
    formError = "Please select reason";
    return;  // Stop here
  }
end note

UI -> Service: **20:** ChangeUserStatusAsync(\n  userId: 5,\n  isActive: **false**,\n  reason: "Teacher Violation",\n  notes: "Violated T&C Section 3.2")
activate Service

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════░
' PHASE 4: DATABASE UPDATE
' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════

rect rgb(255, 250, 200)
    Note over Service, DB
      **PHASE 4: DATABASE UPDATE**
      Service processes block request
    end note
end

Service -> DbContext: **21:** db.Users.FindAsync(userId: 5)
activate DbContext

DbContext -> DB: **22:** SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE id = 5
activate DB

DB --> DbContext: **23:** User entity (John Smith, IsActive=true)
deactivate DB

DbContext --> Service: **24:** User object
deactivate DbContext

Service -> Service: **25:** Check if user exists
note right of Service
  if (user == null) {
    return ApiResponse.Fail(
      "User not found.");
  }
end note

alt ✅ User Found
    Service -> Service: **26a:** Update User Object
    note right of Service
      user.IsActive = false
      user.UpdatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow()
    end note
    
    Service -> DbContext: **27a:** db.Users.Update(user)
    activate DbContext
    
    DbContext -> DB: **28a:** UPDATE users\nSET is_active = false,\n    updated_at = NOW()\nWHERE id = 5
    activate DB
    
    DB --> DbContext: **29a:** 1 row affected
    deactivate DB
    
    DbContext -> DbContext: **30a:** await SaveChangesAsync()
    note right of DbContext
      Commits transaction to PostgreSQL
      Change persisted
    end note
    
    DbContext --> Service: **31a:** SaveSuccessful
    deactivate DbContext
    
    Service -> Service: **32a:** Prepare Success Response
    note right of Service
      ApiResponse<object?>.Ok(null,
        "User blocked successfully.")
    end note
    
    Service --> UI: **33a:** ApiResponse\n{ Success: true,\n  Message: "User blocked successfully." }
    
else ❌ User Not Found
    Service --> UI: **33b:** ApiResponse\n{ Success: false,\n  Message: "User not found." }
end

deactivate Service

' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════
' PHASE 5: UI REACTION & RELOAD
' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════

rect rgb(200, 240, 200)
    Note over UI, DB
      **PHASE 5: UI RESPONSE & RELOAD LIST**
      UI processes response
    end note
end

alt ✅ Block Success
    UI -> UI: **34a:** Close Modal\nCloseAllModals()
    note right of UI
      showBlockModal = false
      selectedUser = null
      blockReason = ""
    end note
    
    UI -> UI: **35a:** Reload User List
    
    UI -> Service: **36a:** GetUsersAsync() [REFRESH]
    activate Service
    
    Service -> DbContext: **37a:** Query users (same as Phase 1)
    activate DbContext
    
    DbContext -> DB: **38a:** SELECT * FROM users WHERE...\nJOIN student_profiles\nJOIN teacher_profiles
    activate DB
    
    DB --> DbContext: **39a:** User records (John now has is_active=false)
    deactivate DB
    
    DbContext --> Service: **40a:** IEnumerable<User>
    deactivate DbContext
    
    Service -> Service: **41a:** Map to DTOs\n(John's Status now = "Blocked")
    
    Service --> UI: **42a:** Updated IEnumerable<UserRowDto>
    deactivate Service
    
    UI -> UI: **43a:** Update Table\nusers = result.ToList()
    
    UI -> UI: **44a:** Highlight blocked user row\n(different styling)
    note right of UI
      CSS class: um-row--blocked
      Visual indicator: red/lock icon
    end note
    
    UI -> UI: **45a:** Display Toast Notification\n"User blocked successfully"
    
    UI --> Admin: **46a:** Show Updated User List\nwith John Smith in "Blocked" status
    
else ❌ Block Failed
    UI -> UI: **34b:** Show Error Toast\nformError = response.Message
    
    UI --> Admin: **35b:** Display Error:\n"User not found" or other error
end

deactivate UI

' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════
' PHASE 6: UNBLOCK (SIMILAR PROCESS)
' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════

rect rgb(200, 240, 200)
    Note over Admin, DB
      **PHASE 6: UNBLOCK USER (Similar Process)**
      When admin clicks "Unblock" on blocked user:
      - Steps 13-20 similar (different modal)
      - ChangeUserStatusAsync(userId, **true**, reason)
      - isActive set to **true** instead of false
      - User status returns to "Active"
    end note
end

' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════
' LEGEND
' ════════════════════════════════░════════════════════

note over Admin, DB
  **LEGEND:**
  
  **Key Transitions:**
  ① Admin triggers action
  ② UI calls Service method
  ③ Service queries/updates database via DbContext
  ④ EF Core translates to SQL
  ⑤ PostgreSQL executes and returns result
  ⑥ Response flows back to UI
  ⑦ UI updates and redisplays data
  
  **Key Objects:**
  • User: { Id, Email, IsActive, DeletedAt, Role }
  • UserRowDto: { Id, Email, Role, Status, Name }
  • ApiResponse<T>: { Success, Message, Data }
  
  **Key Method:**
  UserManagementService.ChangeUserStatusAsync(userId, isActive, reason, notes)
  
  **Key Database:**
  TABLE users(
    id BIGINT PRIMARY KEY,
    email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
    deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL,
    role VARCHAR(50),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    ...
  )
end note

@enduml
